<h2 class="p87">PARENTAL RIGHTS</h2>
<p class="p90">Parents of children under the age of 13 who are users of the Services have certain rights under COPPA, and Herotainment recognizes those rights. Parents can consent to collection and use of a child&rsquo;s personally identifiable information without consenting to the disclosure of information to third parties. Currently the only identifiable information we may collect from children is username, password, gender, birthday and parent&rsquo;s email address. If a parent instructs us, we will delete the information provided during the registration process within a reasonable time period.</p>
<p class="p92"><span class="c0">A child&rsquo;s participation or access to an activity on the Services is not conditioned on their providing more personal information than is reasonably necessary for the activity.</span></p>
<p class="p93"><span class="c0">Parents can review information their children have contributed to the Services, request that Herotainment delete that information, and refuse to allow Herotainment to collect further information from their child by contacting our customer support department by email at info@herotainment.com. Parents should include their child&rsquo;s username and the registered (parent&rsquo;s) email address in the email so we can better assist them with their inquiry or request. Herotainment may ask additional questions or take other steps to verify the identity of parents before responding to a request to review or delete their child&rsquo;s information, or a request to refuse further collection from the child.</span></p>
<h2 class="p94">LINKS TO THIRD PARTY WEB SERVICES</h2>
<p class="p96">We may provide links to third party services, including links from our Shop feature. Through that feature, we let our users know where they can purchase Herotainment merchandise. Before a user can exit our Services, we explain that the user is leaving our Services, and going to the Services of a third party. Once they leave our Services, he or she may submit information to a third party, over whom we have no authority or control, and who may have different information collection and use practices. Users and Parents should always read a company&rsquo;s Privacy Policy carefully, including those companies to whom we provide links, before submitting information to them.</p>
<p class="p98"><span class="c0">We do not store or share your financial information except as described in this Privacy Policy. However, if you bought or otherwise accessed the Services through a third-party distributor such as Apple, Google or Amazon, that company may collect and store your Financial Information. Please review any applicable Distributor&rsquo;s privacy policies to see how it handles your information.</span></p>
<h2 class="p99">INFORMATION SHARING AND DISCLOSURE</h2>
<p class="p101">Herotainment does not share, rent or trade personally identifying information about our registered users, including children under the age of 13, with non-affiliated third parties (i.e., companies who are not one of our corporate affiliates or who are not providing support to the internal operations of our company) for their promotional purposes. Herotainment makes every reasonable effort to disallow and discourage users and children from sharing personally identifying information with each other via the Services features via a filter system and moderators. The only information that can be openly shared in the Services features are screen names (and children are cautioned not to select their real names).</p>
<h2 class="p103">COMMUNITY DISCLOSURES</h2>
<p class="p105"><span class="c0">I</span>f you use a forum or blog on this Service, you should be aware that any personally identifiable information you submit there can be read, collected, or used by other users of these forums, and could be used to send you unsolicited messages. Though we pre-moderate the blog comments and the Forums are pre-moderated and post-moderated, we are not responsible for the personally identifiable information you choose to submit in these forums.</p>
<p class="p107"><span class="c0">If you no longer wish to receive our newsletter and promotional communications, you may opt-out of receiving them by following the instructions included in each newsletter or you may communicate by emailing us at info@herotainment.com &ndash; please type UNSUBSCRIBE in the subject line, or you may contact us in writing by mail to: Herotainment, LLC, 79 Madison Avenue, New York, NY 10016.</span></p>
<h2 class="p108">UPDATING PERSONALLY IDENTIFIABLE INFORMATION</h2>
<p class="p110">If your personally identifiable information changes, or if you no longer desire our service, you may correct, update, amend, delete/remove or deactivate it by emailing our customer support team at info@herotainment.com or by contacting us by mail at the contact information listed below. We will respond to your request to change the information within a reasonable amount of time.</p>
<h2 class="p112">CONFIDENTIAL AND SECURE PERSONAL INFORMATION</h2>
<p class="p114">We work hard to protect your personal information. No method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure, however. Therefore, while we strive to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security. We use both technical and procedural methods to maintain the integrity and security of our databases, including giving users a unique username and password for access to the Services, SSL encryption for data transfer, firewalls, and restricted access to data.</p>
<p class="p116"><span class="c0">However, the safety and security of your information also depends on you. You should never share your password with anyone else and you should always logoff before leaving your computer or mobile device. If you believe someone has unauthorized access to your password or account, please contact us immediately.</span></p>
<p class="p117"><span class="c0">This Service may contain links to other Services operated by third parties that may be of interest to you. When you follow a link and leave this Service, you do so at your own risk because we do not control such third party Services.</span></p>
<p class="p118"><span class="c0">If you have any questions about security on the Services, you can send email us at info@herotainment.com.</span></p>
<h2 class="p119">EFFECTIVE DATE AND CHANGES</h2>
<p class="p121">This Privacy Policy is updated as of January 26, 2016 and applies to all information previously obtained by Herotainment. Herotainment reserves the right to change its Privacy Policy in its sole discretion. In such case, Herotainment will post the new Privacy Policy on the Services and the effective date of the new Privacy Policy will be clearly marked. With respect to children under the age of 13, Herotainment will not use personally identifiable information from such children in ways that are materially different from this version of the Privacy Policy unless the parents are notified of, and consent to, the new changes to the Privacy Policy.</p>
<p class="p123"><span class="c0">Your use of the Services is subject to this Privacy Policy as well as our Terms of Use. Among other things, the Terms of Use establishes disclaimers of warranties, limitations on Herotainment&rsquo;s liability, choice of law and venue, and restrictions on your use of the Services. Please review this Privacy Policy and the Terms of Use carefully, because if you do not agree with our practices, your ultimate choice is not to use this Service.</span></p>
